\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
Shit, I am late. I hope it hasn't been long. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
I was running in the alleys of upper levels when I heard the sound of trumpets  from the newly constructed stadium in a distance. It was standing majestic, touching even the skies. The people arround me were talking about the chariot race that had just finished as I ran past them in my hurry to reach the stadium in time. Apparently Pandav Nakula had won the race and was now being honored by a garland for it. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
I reached the gates of the stadium. They were huge in width and yet there was so musch rush. The whole city, maybe even the whole kingdom was here to see the new princes. The crowds flooded the gates like waves of an ocean and filled the seats .I pushed my way through the crowds to reach a vacant seat on the upper corner when I was stopped by one of the city guards. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
"The common citizens and participating soldiers are remained to be seated on the lower levels. The Upper ones are for high borns and royal blood." The guard said }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
Even here?}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
 This kingdom hasn't changed a bit in all these ten years. }{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
The state of individuals is still decided by their birth. But no matter, that will change today}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
, I promised. I will change this system.  I took my seat in the lowest but nearest section of the stadium grounds. I was too anxious to hold my excitment back. What will be their expressions when they see my arrows?}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
The royal stand decked with tent and seats engraved with gold  leaves and dangling pearls had  some familiar faces. King Dhritrashtra and Queen Ghandhari were occupying their seats at the center. Grandfather Bhisma, now my student-brother was sitting to the right of the king. And an unknown middle aged lady in white silk saree who was unfamiliat was sitting besides Queen Ghandhari. She was fairly old and had no makeup. She was obviously someone important sitting so near to the queen. I didnt know who she was so my atttention went right to Guru Drona who was gracing the seat beside Pitama Bhishma along wth his pony tailed brother-in-law Kripacharya.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
The crowd was cheering as the garland was presented to nakul by drona as he approached him in the royal stand. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
"}{\i\dbch\af4\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9\loch\f4
NAKUL IS ONE OF THE BEST RIDERS THERE IS. HIS SPEED IN BATTLE AND ON MOUNT IS URIVALED IN ALL MY STUDENTS.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\i\dbch\af4\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9\loch\f4
I AM PROUD TO HAVE THE CHANCE TO TRAIN SUCH A KSHATRIYA,}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
" Guru Drona announced for the whole crowd to hear. They went into cheers as he touched his guru's feet and then moved to touch the feet of the woman in white sari. I was perplexed for a moment.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
"}{\i\dbch\af4\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9\loch\f4
Next will be the Gada Yudh}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
" Dronacharya pointed out towards the section where the princes were sitting. Two sections, one of which was so huge and so packed that you can barely make out each individual and another so small that it only had the capacity to hold six-to seven people. So these were the grown up Kauravs and Pandavs. One of the older prince from the kaurav section rose up and at the same time the hulking semi-giant from the pandavs also jumped in. They both grabbed a gadha from thier side and came down on the stadium ground. Though I couldn't recall who the one fighting from Kaurav side was but the one fighting from pandav's was definitly Bheema. I had heard about his tales as how he subdued nagas when he was just a child. It is said that he has the strength of an elephant. The warrior looked strong too.  It was clear from their eyes that they had animosity between them. It wasn't rivalry but a lust for others blood. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
They struck their Gadha in approval and backed away surely measuring each other through their eyes. I remembered how I used to do that when I fought Acharya, }{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
what a fool.}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
 The Kaurav made the first move imbueing his mace with thunder as he rushed forward. Bheem in respond imbued his mace with fire and went full too. Each touch of thier mace was emanating electricity arround. But none of them were ready to back of. It was very similar to how my duels with Acharya went but also very different in the fact though the intent of kill was absent between us, here it radiated like the heat from a forest fire, reaching far and wide. Surely the king had sensed this vibe as even the audience was gasping at each stroke and each dodge performed by the two. After a few minutes they both were bathing in blood, whose it was didn't mattered. The widowed woman sitting beside gandhari had just stood up with her hands on her heart. I figured out in that instant who she was. She was Kunti the mother of the Pandavs, Her worry reflected her feeling, her love for her son.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
They both backed away and gathered thier strength for a minute. Then the next second they both rushed at each other with even more ferocity....}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\kerning1\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang9
